=head1 DESCRIPTION

The pattern configuration for redacting custom data types in session.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 KeywordRegex => Str

The keyword regex for the customer pattern. After there is a match to
the pattern regex, the keyword regex is used to search within the
proximity of the match. If there is a keyword match, then the match is
confirmed. If no keyword regex is provided, the pattern regex match
will automatically be confirmed. The format must follow JavaScript
regex format. The pattern must be enclosed between slashes, and can
have flags behind the second slash. For example,
E<ldquo>/ab+c/giE<rdquo>


=head2 PatternDescription => Str

The pattern description for the customer pattern.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> PatternName => Str

The pattern name for the custom pattern.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> PatternRegex => Str

The pattern regex for the customer pattern. The format must follow
JavaScript regex format. The pattern must be enclosed between slashes,
and can have flags behind the second slash. For example:
E<ldquo>/ab+c/giE<rdquo>.



